## Public Member Functions

### advanceToLowerBound() {#ab7ef8845c21d2c77b26099dc75a66ff5}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>void llvm::CoalescingBitVector&lt; IndexT &gt;::const&#95;iterator::advanceToLowerBound (IndexT Index)</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Advance the iterator to the first set bit AT, OR AFTER, <code>Index</code>.

If no such set bit exists, advance to <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/coalescingbitvector/#a4094e1a4b11c655a8208dd9d7b306c43">end()</a>. This is like std::lower&#95;bound. This is useful if <code>Index</code> is close to the current iterator position. However, unlike <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/coalescingbitvector/#a84519c831af8bdd490359710a57bea17">find()</a>, this has worst-case O(n) performance.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/adt/coalescingbitvector-h/#l00330">330</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/adt/coalescingbitvector-h">CoalescingBitVector.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

</SectionDefinition>

## Private Member Functions

### advanceTo() {#a62d507505ebd54d2afb5492a0d42fc70}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>void llvm::CoalescingBitVector&lt; IndexT &gt;::const&#95;iterator::advanceTo (IndexT Index)</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Advance the iterator to <code>Index</code>, if it is contained within the current interval.

The public-facing method which supports advancing past the current interval is <a href="#ab7ef8845c21d2c77b26099dc75a66ff5">advanceToLowerBound</a>.
